## Reflections on Imperial Fragility

The fall of the Reman Empire teaches a brutal lesson: an empire, however powerful, can collapse in a single night if its continuity rests on a single point of failure — the survival of a bloodline. The assassination of a few individuals is enough to plunge a continent into centuries of darkness.

This lesson resonates across all the eras of Tamriel. The Septim Empire also fell when its line was extinguished. The covenant of Akatosh itself rests on the survival of a bloodline. Fragility is inscribed at the very heart of the system — and those who, like the Dark Brotherhood, understand this fragility hold a disproportionate power relative to their numbers.
